5. Pentakill Yorick {{champion:83}}
I just like standing around and dancing, the change to the music is win.

4. Gatekeeper Galio {{champion:3}}
The updated one, that is. It looks incredible, and it's on a champion I fully intend to play, since he's basically taking Shen's job over at this point.

3. Pool Party Zac {{champion:154}}
Part of me knows that I only value this skin so highly because Riot doesn't give Zac his fair share of skins. But it's also just a really nice skin on its own, and the back animation is the most adorable thing in League of Legends--and yes, I'm including Dragon Trainer Tristana in that list, fite me :|

2. Radiant Wukong {{champion:62}}
I love this skin. It's just so COOL. I immediately stopped using all other Wukong skins once I got this one.

1. Mecha Zero Sion {{champion:14}}
This skin is INCREDIBLE. It's well-done, the theme works amazingly well with Sion, and the car/train hybrid thing simultaneously works well on its own and honors the fact that Sion's ult has been nicknamed "The Pain Train" since his rework. 10/10. I think this is the only 1820 skin I've ever outright paid for, the rest I got from mystery boxes or used RP from tournament victories.
